headline: Super Micro Stock Jumps Again. It’s Starting the Year With Some Wild Swings.
summary: Super Micro Computer  stock was rising on Monday, building on Friday’s double-digit gains.  The stock, which trades under the ticker SMCI, jumped 11% to $36.55 in morning trading.  Super Micro was the most volatile stock in the S&P 500 last year, ahead of the likes of  Palantir Technologies  and  Tesla  Not much has changed so far in 2025.

headline: Nvidia, AMD, other chipmakers gain on Foxconn sales growth
summary: Nvidia (NVDA), Advanced Micro Devices (AMD), and Tawain Semiconductor Manufacturer (TSM) are trading higher in the pre-market session after Foxconn Technology Group (2317.TW) — which trades as Hon Hai Technology Group in China and Taiwan — reported faster-than-expected sales growth boosted by artificial intelligence (AI) hardware demand. Broadcom (AVGO) and Qualcomm (QCOM) shares are on the rise as well. Seana Smith and Brad Smith closely examine the chipmaker stocks' movements on Morning Brief. Semiconductor stocks are also in focus ahead of Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang's keynote at the 2025 Consumer Electronics Show (CES).. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief here. This post was written by Naomi Buchanan.

headline: Super Micro Stock Rises. Why Wild Bouts of Volatility Might Not Be Over Just Yet.
summary: Super Micro Computer Inc.  stock was rising ahead of the opening bell, putting the server maker on course to build on Friday’s double-digit gains.  Super Micro was the most volatile S&P 500 stock last year, ahead of the likes of  Palantir Technologies  and  Tesla  If the start of 2025 is anything to go by, it could carry on swinging wildly for a while yet.  It’s tougher to work out whether it’s worth owning SMCI stock as an investment, considering the issues the company is grappling with.
